## ðŸ§­ Step 1: Subdomain Enumeration & Technology Discovery
### âœ… 1.1 Manual Enumeration (Passive Recon)

These sources help find **historical, indexed, and certificate-based subdomains** without touching the target directly.

**Certificate Transparency & Asset Discovery**

* [https://crt.sh](https://crt.sh)
* [https://search.censys.io](https://search.censys.io)
* [https://cloud.projectdiscovery.io](https://cloud.projectdiscovery.io)

**Threat Intelligence / OSINT**

* [https://www.virustotal.com/gui/home/url](https://www.virustotal.com/gui/home/url)
* [https://securitytrails.com](https://securitytrails.com)
* [https://www.shodan.io](https://www.shodan.io)
* [https://hunter.io](https://hunter.io) (email â†’ domain intel)

**Search Engine Dorking**

```text
site:*.example.com
site:example.com -www
```

---

### âœ… 1.2 Automated Subdomain Enumeration
Automated tools are used to **scale discovery** and avoid missing assets.

**Primary Tools**

* `subfinder` â€“ fast passive enumeration
* `amass` â€“ deep OSINT + DNS-based recon
* `assetfinder` â€“ quick subdomain discovery

**Supplementary / Custom Tools**

* `magicrecon`
* `lostfuzzer.sh`
* `alienvault.sh` (AlienVault OTX)

**DNS Resolution**

* `massdns` â€“ validate discovered subdomains
* `dnsx` â€“ fast DNS resolution with filtering

Example:

```bash
subfinder -d example.com -all | dnsx -silent > alive_subdomains.txt
```

---

## ðŸ§  Step 2: Subdomain Validation & Live Host Detection
After enumeration, identify **which subdomains are alive**.

**Tools**

* `httpx`
* `httprobe`

Example:

```bash
cat subdomains.txt | httpx -sc -title -ip -tech-detect -o live.txt
```

---

## ðŸ§© Step 3: Technology Fingerprinting
Identify frameworks, servers, WAFs, and backend tech.

**Tools**

* `httpx -tech-detect`
* `whatweb`
* `wappalyzer` (browser extension)
* `builtwith.com`

Example:

```bash
httpx -l live.txt -tech-detect -json -o tech.json
```

---

## ðŸ—‚ Step 4: Asset Categorization
Group targets to reduce noise and improve bug quality.

**Examples**

* Authentication portals
* Admin panels
* APIs
* Static assets
* Legacy systems

```bash
grep -i "login\|auth" live.txt > auth_targets.txt
```

---

## ðŸ”— Step 5: URL & Endpoint Discovery (Next Phase)
Once subdomains are ready, move to endpoint discovery.

**Tools**

* `hakrawler`
* `katana`
* `gau`
* `waybackurls`
* `paramspider`

